angleEnd defines the angle of the last stringer element. The angle starting value is taken from the first stringer positioning.
stringer spacing type The spacing can be defined by an angular delta value or a spacing distance and a x reference position

The stringer definition can be used to define one or more fuselage stringer elements. One stringer element is defined by two or more positiongs and can be repeated around the fuselage with a discrete number or a spacing value. The spacing can be a radial angle or distance. For the distance, an additional x position has to be provided to define the fuselage circumfirence.
